- `removeListener(eventType, listener)`: This method should remove the given `listener` from the specified `eventType`. If the `eventType` does not exist or the `listener` is not found, it should do nothing.
- `dispatchEvent(eventType, eventData)`: This method should dispatch the given `eventType` with the provided `eventData` to all the listeners subscribed to that `eventType`.

You should implement the `EventDispatcher` class and its methods to fulfill the requirements.

```javascript
class EventDispatcher {
  constructor() {
    this.listeners = new Map();
  }

  addListener(eventType, listener) {
    if (!this.listeners.has(eventType)) {
      this.listeners.set(eventType, new Set());
    }
    this.listeners.get(eventType).add(listener);
  }

  removeListener(eventType, listener) {
    if (this.listeners.has(eventType)) {
      this.listeners.get(eventType).delete(listener);
    }
  }

  dispatchEvent(eventType, eventData) {
    if (this.listeners.has(eventType)) {
      for (let listener of this.listeners.get(eventType)) {
        listener(eventData);
      }
    }
  }
}

